org.fosstrak.hal.impl.impinj.comm
Class TCPIPProtocol

java.lang.Object
  org.fosstrak.hal.impl.impinj.comm.TCPIPProtocol

public class TCPIPProtocol
extends java.lang.Object

TCPIPProtocol is an interface to an RFID-Reader. It allows to send a request to the reader. The sendRequest method then locks until a response from the reader has arrived or a timeout occured. When terminating the session with the reader one should close the socket with the close method.

Author:
Jonas Haller
